      "span_text": "It is possible that a subset of neurocognitively impaired HIV-infected patients who concurrently had neurological or imaging evidence of cerebrovascular disease were not diagnosed with HAND by definitional criteria, but were instead included, together with those having other neurological comorbidities (e.g. history of moderate or severe head injury, history of learning disability, brain opportunistic diseases, and severe substance use disorders), in a category of neuropsychological impairment due to other causes"
